  "issue_title": "[Bug] Stale-closed PRs skip pull_requests UPSERT, leaving phantom OPEN rows on miner dashboards",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\n`try_add_open_or_closed_pr` in `gittensor/utils/github_api_tools.py:814-817` returns early when a CLOSED PR was created before the 35-day lookback. Introduced by #406 to prevent a fresh credibility penalty when miners close old backlog PRs \u2014 correct in intent. But the early return also skips the `store_pull_requests_bulk` writes in `gittensor/validator/utils/storage.py:58-66`, which only iterate `miner_eval.{merged,open,closed}_pull_requests`. A prior scan already wrote an OPEN row for the PR, and `BULK_UPSERT_PULL_REQUESTS` never fires again, so `pr_state` stays `OPEN` indefinitely. `/miners/{id}/prs` then serves the stale row to the dashboard.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\nOpen `https://gittensor.io/miners/details?githubId=170978465&tab=pull-requests&prStatus=open` (miner `RenzoMXD`). The Open filter shows 7 rows; only 3 are actually open on GitHub. The other 4 were all created before the 35-day cutoff and closed on GitHub within the last 10 days, satisfying the `created_dt < lookback_date_filter` branch and dropped on every subsequent scan:\n\n| PR | Created | GitHub state | Closed | API `prState` |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `grafana/grafana#119774` | 2026-03-07 | closed | 2026-04-23 | OPEN |\n| `we-promise/sure#1133` | 2026-03-06 | closed | 2026-04-16 | OPEN |\n| `eigent-ai/eigent#1375` | 2026-02-26 | closed | 2026-04-23 | OPEN |\n| `eigent-ai/eigent#1381` | 2026-02-26 | closed | 2026-04-24 | OPEN |\n\n## Expected\n\n`pr_state` in the `pull_requests` row tracks the real GitHub state regardless of scoring inclusion. Credibility math untouched (#406 intent preserved).\n\n## Actual\n\nStale rows persist at `OPEN`. The PR table on the dashboard shows 7 Open for this miner; the MinerScoreCard header tile (driven by `minerStats.totalOpenPrs`, currently 3) disagrees with the table \u2014 7 vs 3. Same pattern affects any miner with long-running PRs that eventually close.\n\n## Additional Context\n\n**No schema change required.** Fix direction: decouple logging from scoring. Route skipped PRs into a log-only bucket on `MinerEvaluation` that `store_pull_requests_bulk` also writes, and extend the `total_*_prs` properties to include it. Reuses the existing `pull_requests` table, existing `BULK_UPSERT_PULL_REQUESTS` query, existing columns \u2014 no `ALTER TABLE`, no new columns, no migration. The only DB-level effect is that rows currently frozen at `pr_state='OPEN'` start getting UPSERT-ed to their real state.",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-04T16:31:08.000Z",
